fields.description:
As long as the request is syntactically correct, attempting to delete a route from a nonexistent routing table results in HTTP 500 responses.

{code}
% bin/euca-delete-route rtb-00000000 -r 0.0.0.0/32                 
euca-delete-route: error (InternalError): Error updating route-table 'rtb-00000000'
{code}

The correct response is a 400 with code {{InvalidRoute.NotFound}}:

{code}
% bin/euca-delete-route rtb-00000000 -r 0.0.0.0/32 --region us-east-1
euca-delete-route: error (InvalidRoute.NotFound): no route with destination-cidr-block 0.0.0.0/32 in route table rtb-00000000
{code}

fields.summary: Trying to delete entries from a nonexistent routing table results in 500s

comments.body:
The reported issue addressed and a similar issue with network acl entries is also fixed:

{code}
# 
# 
# euca-delete-route rtb-00000000 -r 0.0.0.0/32
euca-delete-route: error (InvalidRoute.NotFound): no route with destination-cidr-block 0.0.0.0/32 in route table rtb-00000000
# 
# 
# euca-delete-network-acl-entry -n 100 acl-00000000
euca-delete-network-acl-entry: error (InvalidNetworkAclEntry.NotFound): Entry not found for number 100 in network acl acl-00000000
# 
# 
{code}

Verified that error is consistent with AWS when trying to delete a route from a non-existent route table and when trying to delete a network ACL entry from a non-existent network ACL.
{noformat}
Name        : eucalyptus
Version     : 4.4.0
Release     : 0.25773.140.20170128gitc9a422a.el7
Architecture: x86_64
Install Date: Sun 29 Jan 2017 06:47:15 AM PST
{noformat}

{noformat}
# euca-delete-route -r 2.2.2.0/30 rtb-1a45b4fd --region testuser1@
euca-delete-route: error (InvalidRoute.NotFound): Route not found for cidr: 2.2.2.0/30
# 
# euca-delete-route -r 2.2.2.0/30 rtb-12345678 --region testuser1@
euca-delete-route: error (InvalidRoute.NotFound): no route with destination-cidr-block 2.2.2.0/30 in route table rtb-12345678
# 
# euca-delete-network-acl-entry -n 10 acl-12345678 --region testuser1@
euca-delete-network-acl-entry: error (InvalidNetworkAclEntry.NotFound): Entry not found for number 10 in network acl acl-12345678
{noformat}
Moving 4.4.0 Issues from Release Pending to Resolved
